OL,3,CBoy's epileptic seizures 'cured' by
OL,4,Cpioneering brain surgery
OL,6,FA robot carefully inserts electrodes
OL,7,Finto a patient's head to locate the
OL,8,Fbit of the brain causing their
OL,9,Fseizures - a procedure called
OL,10,Fstereoelectroencephalography.
OL,12,FThen in a second procedure, that piece
OL,13,Fof brain can be removed. The risks of
OL,14,Fneurosurgery are huge, but so are the
OL,15,Fpotential benefits.
OL,17,F"It's become clear how incredibly
OL,18,Feffective epilepsy surgery is and yet
OL,19,Fhow infrequently it's actually
OL,20,Fundertaken in the UK," said Finley's
OL,21,Fsurgeon, Professor Mike Carter.
