OL,3,CBoy's epileptic seizures 'cured' by
OL,4,Cpioneering brain surgery
OL,6,FHe spends a lot of his time spreading
OL,7,Fthe word to clinicians in the region,
OL,8,Fexplaining that many more young
OL,9,Fpatients could benefit in the way
OL,10,FFinley has.
OL,12,FSevere epilepsy can make life very
OL,13,Fdifficult. Like many children with the
OL,14,Fcondition, Finley had fallen behind at
OL,15,Fschool.
OL,17,FAccording to the charity Epilepsy
OL,18,FAction, two-thirds of working-age
OL,19,Fadults with epilepsy are unemployed,
OL,20,Ffar more than for those with most
OL,21,Fother disabilities.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
